<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="482" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1436,1546,1973]" pageId="11" pageNumber="482">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,344,1660,1685]" pageId="11" pageNumber="482">Description.</emphasis>
Body shape eel-like, moderately compressed, elongated and attenuated to the caudal peduncle; top of snout and head scaleless, opercle scaleless; the preoral portion of the snout is short, contained 3.8 and 4.7 times in the snout length; first dorsal ray very short and vestigial; pelvic fins lie well in advance of dorsal origin; palatine tooth patches separate; pyloric caeca black and anal opening white surrounded by a dark field. The main morphometric and meristic characteristics are presented in 
<tableCitation box="[813,898,1804,1829]" captionStart="TABLE 7" captionStartId="12.[151,239,152,175]" captionTargetBox="[159,1358,234,1362]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="TABLE 7. Comparison of morphometric, meristic data and respective body proportions for specimens of Aldrovandia phalacra." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/DF376615FFD9FFE6FCE4FF39FF07FF04" pageId="11" pageNumber="482" tableUuid="DF376615FFD9FFE6FCE4FF39FF07FF04">Table 7</tableCitation>
.
</paragraph>
